    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And when there was an assault made,.... Or a strong bias and inclination were in the minds, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "both of the Gentiles, and also of the Jews, with their rulers; who encouraged them in it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to use them despitefully, and to stone them; not only to give them reproachful language, but to smite, buffet, and scourge them, and to stone them for blasphemy, which was a punishment among the Jews for such causes. ",
        "children": [
